trend_summary: Built-up area steadily expands, led by the eastern industrial core and ribbon growth along main roads. Forest and farmland are incrementally cleared for warehouses, parking, and curvilinear housing tracts. Road density rises and a new southeast arterial appears, shifting the landscape from predominantly rural to a mixed, medium-density suburban setting.
notable_changes: Eastern industrial/commercial zone roughly doubles in roof area, adding large white warehouses and parking lots.
New residential subdivisions with cul-de-sac layouts emerge north of the central highway, replacing forest.
Diagonal southeast arterial is widened and gains a new interchange, improving regional connectivity.
Central forest patches are cleared between early and mid images, opening land for construction and agriculture.
Western agricultural blocks show intensified cultivation, while some marginal fields are later reforested.
